## Documentation lookup rule

Project documentation is available through multiple MCP servers.
Use `sajtmaskin-mpc` for project-specific docs; use the dedicated MCP
servers for external platform docs (see `mcp-docs-routing.mdc`).

### Local docs (`sajtmaskin-mpc`)

- Entrypoint: `services/mpc/server.mjs`
- Docs directory: `services/mpc/docs/` and `LLM/`
- Exposes **resources only** (no tools) via `docs://local/{name}`
- Contains: v0 prompt guide, architecture notes, AI SDK references, error playbook

### When to consult local docs

- User-facing page building / site generation
- v0 Platform API patterns and prompt strategies
- AI SDK usage and streaming patterns
- General integration details specific to this project

### When to use other MCP servers instead

- **v0 code generation or chat management** -> use the `v0` MCP server directly
- **shadcn/ui component lookup or installation** -> use the `shadcn` MCP server
- **Vercel deploy/project management** -> use the `Vercel` MCP server
- **OpenAI API docs** -> use `openaiDeveloperDocs`
